# Release + publish — agent checklist

> **Trigger:** version bump, `git tag`, npm publish, GitHub Release, `release.yml`, CHANGELOG.

## Non-negotiable order

1. `pnpm verify` green on `developing`
2. PR `developing` → `main` (CI `test` + approval)
3. **Bump version** in **all six** publishable packages (same semver)
4. **CHANGELOG** — move `[Unreleased]` → `[X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD`
5. Commit + merge to `main`
6. **Only then** create and push git tag `vX.Y.Z`
7. Release workflow publishes npm + GitHub Release
8. Sync `developing` from `main`

**NEVER** push a tag before step 3–5. **NEVER** run `pnpm publish` locally — CI-only (`scripts/assert-ci-publish.mjs`).

## Files that MUST match

| File | Field |
|------|--------|
| `packages/br-validators/package.json` | `"version"` |
| `apps/cli/package.json` | `"version"` |
| `packages/br-validators-zod/package.json` | `"version"` |
| `packages/br-validators-rhf/package.json` | `"version"` |
| `packages/br-validators-express/package.json` | `"version"` |
| `packages/br-validators-vue/package.json` | `"version"` |
| Git tag | `v` + same semver (e.g. `v1.6.1`) |

## Pre-tag verification (run before `git tag`)

```bash
VERSION="1.6.1"   # planned release — no v prefix
for PKG in packages/br-validators apps/cli packages/br-validators-zod packages/br-validators-rhf packages/br-validators-express packages/br-validators-vue; do
  V=$(jq -r .version "$PKG/package.json")
  test "$VERSION" = "$V" || { echo "MISMATCH $PKG=$V"; exit 1; }
done
echo "OK"
git tag -l "v$VERSION"     # must be empty before new tag
```

## Tag + publish (automated — CI only)

```bash
git checkout main && git pull
git tag -a v1.6.1 -m "Release v1.6.1"
git push origin v1.6.1
```

Workflow: `.github/workflows/release.yml` — requires secret **`NPM_TOKEN`**. Publishes all six packages; sets npm **`latest`**.

**Re-run:** Actions → Release → workflow_dispatch with tag `v1.6.1`.

## Common mistakes

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Tag `v1.6.1` but `package.json` still `1.6.0` | Bump all six `package.json`, merge `main`, delete bad tag, retag |
| Tag on wrong commit (old code) | Delete remote tag + release; tag `main` HEAD after merge |
| Local `pnpm publish` | Blocked by design — push tag or re-run Release workflow |
| Re-tag same version already on npm | Bump to next patch/prerelease — or re-run workflow (skips existing versions) |
| Any package version differs | Set all six to identical semver before tag |
| `express` / `vue` 404 on npm | Fix `NPM_TOKEN` — token must allow **create** on `@br-validators/*` |

## Agent duties on release tasks

1. Bump **all six** `package.json` files in the same commit.
2. Update `CHANGELOG.md` for the release scope only.
3. Run pre-tag verification commands; report mismatch before tagging.
4. Do **not** paste or commit `NPM_TOKEN` — GitHub secret only.
5. After release, confirm: `npm view @br-validators/core version` (and express, vue).

**Docs:** `docs/BRANCHING.md`, `docs/VERSIONING.md` — **Troubleshooting:** `npm-publish-ci.mdc`
